About 60 learners from a south Johannesburg school were rushed to hospital earlier this week after eating sweets distributed by an unknown man. JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng Education Department has confirmed that all pupils from the Suidheuwels Primary School, south of Johannesburg, who were hospitalised earlier this week after eating sweets laced with drugs have now been discharged.About 60 pupils from the school were rushed to hospital earlier this week after complaining of stomach cramps and vomiting.Two of them were admitted in a critical condition.It s understood an unknown man has been distributing the sweets to pupils in the area.The department's Oupa Bodibe said: All the children were discharged yesterday, even those who were critical. Now that they are out of hospital, we hope they will be able to identify the perpetrator. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)